Get Build DATA

get_data <- function(release, week) {
  r <- NA 
  for (i in 1:week) {
    print(paste('data/r', release, '_w', i,'.csv', sep=''))
    loc <- cbind(release,i, paste(release,i,sep="."), read.csv(file=paste('data/r', release, '_w', i,'.csv', sep=''), sep=',', header=T))
    colnames(loc)[1:3] <- c("release","week","rw")
    
    if(i==1) {
      r <- rbind(r, loc)
    }
    else {
      inter_c <- intersect(colnames(r), colnames(loc))
      r <- rbind(r[,inter_c], loc[,inter_c])
    }
  }
  r
}

clean_data <- function(data) {
  data <- data[which(data$branch %in% c("try","mozilla-inbound","mozilla-central")),]
  data <- data[data$product %in% c("firefox","Firefox"),]
  data <- data[-which(data$revision == "None"),]
  data$revision_12C <- substr(data$revision, 0,12)
  data <- data[which(data$reason == "scheduler"),]
  
  if(!"count_elements" %in% colnames(data)) {
    count_elements <- rep(1, nrow(data))
    data <- cbind(data, count_elements)
  }
  if(!"TimeSec" %in% colnames(data)) {
    TimeSec <- as.POSIXlt(data[, "endtime"]) - as.POSIXlt(data[, "starttime"])
    data <- cbind(data, TimeSec)
  }
  
  platform <- c("mac", "win", "linux", "emulator", "android", "ubuntu")
  grepPlatform <- data$platform
  grep.ubuntu <- grepl("ubuntu", tolower(data$platform))
  grepPlatform[grep.ubuntu] <- "linux"
  
  grepPlatform <- apply(sapply(platform, function(x) grepl(x, tolower(grepPlatform))), 1, function(x) {
    if(sum(x) == 0) "other"
    else if(sum(x) != 1) "too many"
    else platform[x]
  })
  data <- cbind(data, grepPlatform)
  
  data <- data[-which(is.na(data$TimeSec) | data$TimeSec == 0),] # ATTENTION vire beaucoup de data!!!
  
  data$branch <- factor(data$branch)
  # data$reasonAbs <- factor(data$reasonAbs)
  data$reason <- factor(data$reason)
  data$revision_12C <- substr(data$revision, 0,12)
  data$revision_12C <- factor(data$revision_12C)
  data[,c("release","week","rw","date","starttime","endtime","branch","platform","grepPlatform",
          "product","reason","result","buildername","revision","revision_12C","got_revision","who",
          "commit_titles","count_elements","comments","TimeSec")]
}

want <- c("release","week","rw","date","starttime","endtime","branch","platform","grepPlatform",
          "product","reason","reasonAbs","result","buildername","revision","revision_12C","got_revision","who",          
          "commit_titles","count_elements","comments","TimeSec","count_elements","grepPlatform")

Get Push/commit Data

get_pushes <- function(branch, dates)  {
  r <- NA 
  count <- 0
  for (i in 2:length(dates)) {
    loc <- read.csv(file=paste('data/pushes_', branch, '_', dates[i-1], '_', dates[i], '.csv', sep=''), sep=',', header=T)
    loc$uid <- loc$uid + count
    count <- max(loc$uid)
    r  <- rbind(r, loc)
  }
  r[2:nrow(r),]
}

count.commits <- function(data, branch) {
  nbr.commits <- aggregate(data$revision_12C, list(data$uid), length)
  branch.count <- sapply(nbr.commits[,"x"], function(x) x:1) #c(x, rep(0,x-1)))
  count <- c()
  for (i in branch.count) {
    count <- c(count, i)
  }
  res <- cbind(data, count, branch)
  # res[res$count > 0,]
  res
}

if(compute) {
  dates <- as.Date('2014-12-11')
  month(dates) <- month(dates) +0:14
  dates <- c(dates, as.Date('2016-02-29'))
  
  pushes_try <- get_pushes("try", dates)
  pushes_mozilla_central <- get_pushes("mozilla-central", dates)
  pushes_mozilla_inbound <- get_pushes("mozilla-inbound", dates)
  
  count.commits.on.try <- count.commits(pushes_try, "try")
  count.commits.on.mozilla.inbound <- count.commits(pushes_mozilla_inbound, "mozilla-inbound")
  count.commits.on.mozilla.central <- count.commits(pushes_mozilla_central, "mozilla-central")
  
  
  count.commits.mega <- rbind(count.commits.on.try, count.commits.on.mozilla.inbound, count.commits.on.mozilla.central)
}

Number of builds by push

aggr.build.push <- function(data, rw, BRANCH = NA, FUN=NA) {
  if(!is.na(BRANCH)) {
    data <- data[data$branch == BRANCH,]
    rw   <- rw[rw$branch == BRANCH,]
  }
  if(is.na(FUN)) {
    data.build.push <- aggregate(data$revision_12C, list(data$revision_12C, data$branch), length)
  }
  else {
    data.build.push <- aggregate(data$TimeSec, list(data$revision_12C, data$branch), FUN)
  }
  colnames(data.build.push) <- c("revision_12C", "branch", "nbr")
  
  rw <- rw$rw
  cbind(data.build.push, rw)
}
print.boxplot<- function(data, title ="Number of builds by push", BRANCH=NA, release="36 to 45", OUT=T, LOG="y", col="orange") {
  yaxis <- title 
  if(is.na(BRANCH)) {
    title <- paste(title, "on the branches of interest \n by week of the", release,"release.", sep=" ")
  }
  else {
    title <- paste(title, "on the", BRANCH, "\n branch by week of the", release,"release.", sep= " ")
  }
 
  boxplot(data$nbr ~ data$rw, 
          main=title, 
          xlab="Weeks", 
          ylab=yaxis,
          outline=OUT, log=LOG,col=col)
}

Number of commit by push

count.commits <- function(data, commits, rw=early_week, BRANCH=NA) {
  if(!is.na(BRANCH)) {
    data <- data[data$branch == BRANCH,]
    rw   <- rw[rw$branch == BRANCH,]
  }
  aggr.data <- aggregate(data$count_elements, list(data$revision_12C, data$branch), function(x) max(as.integer(x)))
  
  colnames(aggr.data) <- c("revision_12C", "branch", "count_elements")

  count <- rep(0, nrow(aggr.data))
  for(branch in c("try", "mozilla-inbound", "mozilla-central")) {
    this.branch <- aggr.data$branch == branch
    count.commits.this.branch <- commits[count.commits.mega$branch == branch,]
    
    in.pushes <- aggr.data$revision_12C %in% count.commits.this.branch$revision_12C & this.branch

    count[in.pushes] <- sapply(aggr.data[in.pushes, "revision_12C"], function(x) count.commits.this.branch[as.character(count.commits.this.branch$revision_12C) == as.character(x), "count"])
  }
  
  res <- c()
  for(i in count) {
    res <- c(res, i)
  }
  count<- res 
  
  if(BRANCH == "try") {
    count <- count -1
  }
  
  print(sum(count<=0) / length(count))
  
  count[count <= 0] <- aggr.data$count_elements[count <= 0]
  
  nbr <- count
  rw <- rw$rw
  aggr.data <- cbind(aggr.data, nbr, rw)
}

if(compute) {

  commit.mozilla.central <- count.commits(mega_branches, count.commits.mega, BRANCH="mozilla-central")
}

Number of build by commit

nbr.by.nbr <- function(data.build.push, data.commit.push) {
  nbr <- data.build.push$nbr / data.commit.push$nbr
  cbind(data.build.push[,c("revision_12C","branch","rw")], nbr)
}

if(compute) {
  build.commit.try <- nbr.by.nbr(build.push.try, commit.try)
  build.commit.mozilla.inbound <- nbr.by.nbr(build.push.mozilla.inbound, commit.mozilla.inbound)
  build.commit..mozilla.central <- nbr.by.nbr(build.push.mozilla.central, commit.mozilla.central)
}

new_names<-as.matrix(c("id", "revision_12C","start_time", "end_time", "machine_aws", "machine_aws"))

r <- c()
for (day in 1:7) {
    loc <- read.csv(file=paste('data/machine_', day, '.csv', sep=''), sep='\t', header=T)
    colnames(loc) <- unique(new_names[colnames(loc),])
    
    r  <- rbind(r, cbind(loc, day))
}

machine.day <- table(r$day,r$machine_aws)
machine <- table(r$machine_aws)

price <- c(.239, .997, .848, .212, .980, .240, .308, .308, 3.744, 0.936, .896, 1.064, .266, 0, 000, 000, 6.284)

price %*% t(machine.day) / rowSums(machine.day[,price > 0])
##       
##            1     2     3     4     5     6     7
##   [1,] 0.349 0.349 0.347 0.367 0.358 0.343 0.344
mean.price <- price %*% machine / sum(machine[price > 0])

Price by commit

sumTimeH <- function(x) {
  sum(x) / (60.0*60.0) * mean.price
}

if(compute) {
  price.push.try <- aggr.build.push(mega_branches, early_week, BRANCH="try", FUN=sumTimeH)
  price.push.mozilla.inbound <- aggr.build.push(mega_branches, early_week, BRANCH="mozilla-inbound", FUN=sumTimeH)
  price.push.mozilla.central <- aggr.build.push(mega_branches, early_week, BRANCH="mozilla-central", FUN=sumTimeH)
  
  price.commit.try <- nbr.by.nbr(price.push.try, commit.try)
  price.commit.mozilla.inbound <- nbr.by.nbr(price.push.mozilla.inbound, commit.mozilla.inbound)
  price.commit.mozilla.central <- nbr.by.nbr(price.push.mozilla.central, commit.mozilla.central)
}
